Movie: Paul Robeson: Tribute to an Artist

Review: I’m from San Francisco and never really learned much about Harvey Milk — I kind of knew he was the first openly gay public official etc., and that was it. It was awesome to hear how central solidarity was to his politics. The shots of the candlelight march after Milk and Moscone’s deaths down Market Street were beautiful.
I didn’t finish it all in one sitting but it’s a new all time favorite
Very beautifully shot, great acting, just a bit slow for me
Watched it over the last couple days.
